Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.39,0:00:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,There is nothing to debate!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.55,0:00:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I merely punished them for their folly!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.10,0:00:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You wolf in sheep's clothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.81,0:00:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Go back to hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.15,0:00:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, having killed me,\Nyou and I are the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.78,0:00:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,May you burn\Nwith the rest of the criminals.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.70,0:00:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I must live with my sin now.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.17,0:00:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,For the rest of my life!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.18,0:00:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday's play was so good.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.18,0:01:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You should have come, Violet.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.77,0:01:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If you mean Red Devil,\NI am reading the play now.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.14,0:01:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so jealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.56,0:01:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I would have loved to scribe\Nfor Oscar Webster.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.82,0:01:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It means you get to read\Nhis new work first, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.15,0:01:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be his first new work in a while\Nwhen he finishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.74,0:01:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,"Ah, I must live with my sin now.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.50,0:01:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,For the rest of my life."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.05,0:03:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are the letter requests.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.18,0:03:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,This many?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.31,0:03:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There have been more requests for Violet\Nsince the published love letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.48,0:03:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.23,0:03:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you talk to her about her major?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.23,0:03:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.57,0:03:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I only ask because she seems\Nto be lost in her thoughts lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.95,0:03:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,GENETRIX\NROSWELL REGION
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.35,0:03:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.77,0:03:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The Auto Memory Doll service.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.85,0:03:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.36,0:03:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a pleasure to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.15,0:04:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I will travel anywhere\Nto meet your request.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.15,0:04:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Auto Memory Doll
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.62,0:04:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Violet Evergarden at your service.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.87,0:04:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a girl standing there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.37,0:04:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,She had the same hair color\Nas the girl I wanted to see again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.88,0:04:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't even say her name\Nbecause it makes me so sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.30,0:04:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What a surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.51,0:04:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't expecting such a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.18,0:04:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If I am not to your liking,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.51,0:04:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I can arrange for another Doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.60,0:04:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,No, as long as you can type.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.94,0:04:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,My health hasn't been the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.56,0:04:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I am terribly sorry,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.48,0:04:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,but I ask that you refrain from alcohol\Nwhile we work.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.74,0:04:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't write unless I drink!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.20,0:04:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I will be the one writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.99,0:04:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Then let's start working tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.87,0:04:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You're being a little difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.09,0:05:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,-Will we be writing in this room?\N-Either here or the terrace.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.59,0:05:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a study,\Nbut it's a little too cramped.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.51,0:05:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.02,0:05:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,-What happened to your hand?\N-I lost it in the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.81,0:05:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it will not affect my work.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.03,0:05:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.78,0:05:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I have cleaned the area\Nfor a better writing environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.37,0:05:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I brought my own typewriter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.04,0:05:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have any typing paper?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.75,0:05:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,No. They sell it at the store by the port.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.21,0:05:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Go buy some.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.05,0:05:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And dinner, too, while you're at it.\NI want carbonara.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.80,0:05:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.18,0:05:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I am a scribe, not a maid.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.97,0:05:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You're being difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.31,0:06:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got all the ingredients\Nyou need here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.02,0:06:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.19,0:06:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong? Is there something on it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.15,0:06:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I was just wondering\Nhow I am supposed to cook this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.41,0:06:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You crack the egg and separate the yolk.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.29,0:06:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yolk?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.46,0:06:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.55,0:06:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I am trying my hand at cooking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.06,0:06:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's pretty good for your first try.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.77,0:06:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,-Are you not having any?\N-I will have some later.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.61,0:06:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.17,0:07:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.14,0:07:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the alcohol that was here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.35,0:07:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I hid it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.35,0:07:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,They will hinder the writing process.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.06,0:07:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And also, it is not good for your health.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.15,0:07:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I will keep them in my possession for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.65,0:07:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Next is Olive's line.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.53,0:07:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,"We must cross this valley of fire
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.41,0:07:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to get the sword\Nto slay the monster."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.41,0:07:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Stage direction. "Enter a water spirit."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.13,0:07:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The spirit's line.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.92,0:07:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,"I will extinguish this fire for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.30,0:07:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you will be able\Nto cross this valley."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.67,0:07:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So, they will be able to cross it?\NThank goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.59,0:07:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Stage directions.\N"The burning fire is extinguished."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.76,0:08:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,How will it be extinguished?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.31,0:08:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If they pull in the red cloth\Nthat is waving around on the stage,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.98,0:08:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it will look like it's been put out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.27,0:08:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.07,0:08:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.40,0:08:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it good?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.32,0:08:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,How do I put this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.12,0:08:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.91,0:08:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like I'm going through\Nthe experience
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.54,0:08:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,even though it never really happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.21,0:08:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I find myself feeling\Nmuch like this girl, Olive.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.25,0:08:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Feeling happy, and feeling sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.97,0:08:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Feeling uncertain.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.09,0:08:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.22,0:08:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because you are feeling\Nwhat the protagonist Olive is feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.10,0:08:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You feel empathy towards Olive.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.73,0:08:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm relieved that you feel that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.78,0:08:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my first time\Nwriting a children's play.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.58,0:09:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Will Olive be able\Nto cross the valley of fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.66,0:09:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,find the sword,\Nand slay the monster after this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.04,0:09:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but in the process, she loses\Nher power to speak with the spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.38,0:09:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.63,0:09:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Then how will she return home?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.51,0:09:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,She already lost her boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.18,0:09:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't come up with that yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.52,0:09:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You must.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.02,0:09:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.77,0:09:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,or she can't return to her father\Nwho is waiting for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.44,0:09:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you come up with an idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.91,0:09:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The weather is nice today.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.49,0:09:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's too good.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.04,0:09:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.54,0:09:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.13,0:09:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's just a parasol.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.67,0:09:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.34,0:10:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a really beautiful parasol.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.48,0:10:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I need...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.35,0:10:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,a little break.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.24,0:10:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,One day...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.87,0:10:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I promise to show you one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.75,0:10:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.71,0:10:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.38,0:10:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.88,0:10:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,-I shouldn't have...\N-That's enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.22,0:10:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.51,0:10:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.27,0:10:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the play will not be completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.44,0:10:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Olive's story will never be completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.15,0:10:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, is there something\Nyou're hiding from me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.99,0:11:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have the ability\Nto sense those emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.66,0:11:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.29,0:11:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't write anything anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.92,0:11:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can't let it end like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.80,0:11:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's why
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.22,0:11:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I would finish\Nthe story I told Olivia.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.26,0:11:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Olivia?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.22,0:11:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.10,0:11:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,My daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.48,0:11:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I moved here with my daughter\Nafter I lost my wife to an illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.07,0:11:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This used to be our summer home.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.78,0:11:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I think she was sad not having a mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.62,0:11:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.16,0:11:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But she never showed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.66,0:11:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather, she always helped me\Nso I could focus on my work.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.96,0:12:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,My daughter's favorite things\Nwere a frilled parasol
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.38,0:12:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and water birds.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.39,0:12:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.56,0:12:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so jealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.31,0:12:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to try crossing this lake, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.64,0:12:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think I could walk on those leaves?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.07,0:12:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe if you let the wind carry you\Nwith your parasol.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.49,0:12:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Olivia!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.12,0:12:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.87,0:12:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to walk across this lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.42,0:12:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I promise to show you one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.38,0:12:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.76,0:12:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.84,0:12:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,after arguing with the doctors,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.97,0:12:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided to bring her back here\Nto spend what time she had left.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.31,0:12:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It was good to see her smile again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.40,0:13:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Our days were quiet and warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.11,0:13:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.95,0:13:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,my only hope...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.87,0:13:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does God continue to take away\Nwhat's most precious to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.25,0:13:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Parting with someone\Nwho is important to you...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.46,0:13:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Never being able to see them again...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.51,0:13:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I never knew it was so sad...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.80,0:13:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and painful.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.03,0:13:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry for earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.65,0:13:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you are the one in pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.53,0:13:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I apologize for being the one\Nto lose composure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.62,0:13:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I will finish it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.58,0:13:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Olive's story.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.67,0:14:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The girl will reach her home\Nand reunite with her father.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.29,0:14:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how difficult the adventure,\Nshe will get a happy ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.59,0:14:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Both the protagonist and audience\Nwill be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.93,0:14:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I will make it happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.64,0:14:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The monster falls.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.94,0:14:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Olive.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.52,0:14:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,"We finally slayed the monster."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.86,0:14:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Water spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.36,0:14:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,"You did well."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.94,0:14:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Wind spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.61,0:14:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,"We must return to the spirit realm."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.16,0:14:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire spirit. "This is goodbye."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.54,0:14:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Olive stands frozen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.37,0:14:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, how do we get Olive home\Nfrom here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.04,0:14:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Since her boat sank,\Nwill she take a plane?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.47,0:14:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Something a little more imaginative.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.93,0:14:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,She could fly home if she were a bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.56,0:14:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,-What about flying with a parasol?\N-You cannot fly with a parasol.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.69,0:15:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.98,0:15:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The wind spirit appears before her\None last time and says,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.06,0:15:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,"Olive, open your parasol."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.99,0:15:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you try opening the parasol for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.37,0:15:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,"That parasol is your wings.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.66,0:15:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll be carried away\Nif you fly too high.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.08,0:15:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So, step on the ocean's waves,\Nthe river's rocks,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.92,0:15:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and the fallen leaves on the lake."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.67,0:15:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a wonderful idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.42,0:15:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Right? After returning home,\NOlive reunites with her father.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.97,0:15:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And the first thing she says when they're\Nreunited after crossing the ocean is...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.43,0:15:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What should it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.02,0:15:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,"I'm home."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.43,0:15:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,No, "Father?"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.02,0:15:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have writer's block again?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.69,0:15:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you walk towards me from over there?\NI'd like to visualize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.03,0:15:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I can do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.53,0:15:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Across the fallen leaves on the lake\Nif you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.83,0:15:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.04,0:16:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that last bit was just...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.14,0:16:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so jealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.02,0:16:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to try crossing this lake, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.90,0:16:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think I could walk on those leaves?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.78,0:16:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,One day...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.78,0:16:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I promise to show you one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.74,0:16:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.62,0:16:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,How I wish I could hear you call me that\Na thousand times more.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.46,0:16:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.80,0:16:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you didn't have to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.05,0:17:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If only you could have lived...\Ngrown up...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.56,0:17:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,How I wished that for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.96,0:17:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.38,0:17:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe I made three whole steps.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.39,0:17:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.68,0:17:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.47,0:17:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you feeling ill?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.35,0:17:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,After granting me this miracle,\NI told her,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.07,0:17:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,"I don't believe there is a God,\Nbut if there were, it would be you."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.03,0:18:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure I can have this parasol?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.54,0:18:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.83,0:18:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,-I thought I could fly a little further.\N-You went far enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.75,0:18:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You were able to fulfill\NOlivia's "one day" wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.59,0:18:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,One day?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.22,0:18:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Farewell.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.60,0:18:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for using\Nour Auto Memory Doll service.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.52,0:18:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,No, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.19,0:18:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Violet Evergarden.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.91,0:18:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,With the very hand\Nthat took the lives of so many,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.96,0:18:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you write letters\Nthat bring people together?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.96,0:18:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't realize that\Nyour body is on fire and burning up
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.92,0:18:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the things that you did.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.68,0:19:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,-I'm not...\N-You are burning.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.30,0:19:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll understand what I said someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.85,0:19:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you'll realize for the first time\Nthat you have many burns.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.65,0:19:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Major.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.99,0:19:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Live.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.61,0:19:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I allowed?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.74,0:19:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Be free.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.33,0:19:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I was used as a weapon to kill people.\NDo I deserve to live?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.25,0:19:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I've probably taken away\Nso many "one day" wishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.51,0:19:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And those people\Nmost likely had loved ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.22,0:19:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not burning.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.72,0:19:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.22,0:19:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not burning.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.73,0:19:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.23,0:19:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The fire is spreading across my body\Nfrom all the things I've done.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.23,0:19:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I am on fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.67,0:20:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.17,0:20:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If it isn't you, Violet!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.42,0:20:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Madam.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.96,0:20:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Please forgive me\Nfor being disrespectful before.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.47,0:20:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I sincerely apologize\Nfor hurting your feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.93,0:20:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Violet, you don't have to apologize\Nfor that. Please stop bowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.11,0:20:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so thankful\Nto see how far you've come.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.49,0:20:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I am sure Gilbert can rest in peace, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.03,0:20:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Rest in peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.79,0:20:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You said he was alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.83,0:20:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The major is safe, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.09,0:20:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.55,0:21:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He's alive, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.59,0:21:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. I just couldn't\Nbring myself to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.10,0:21:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,After the Final Battle of Intense,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.94,0:21:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,you were found alone on the ground\Nunder a church.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.94,0:21:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Most likely, he pushed you away\Nright before it was bombarded.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.74,0:21:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,While we didn't find his body,\Nwe did find his ID tag under the debris.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.62,0:21:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,-And so, he was deemed missing in action.\N-So, we do not know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.12,0:21:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,-But given the situation...\N-I'm sure the major is alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.80,0:21:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,-Violet...\N-He's alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.97,0:21:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Violet, please understand,\Nhe's already...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.30,0:21:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't. I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.18,0:21:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,How could I be the only one to survive?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.77,0:21:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The major was there with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.19,0:21:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And he...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.40,0:22:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Violet, you have to accept it,\Neven if it's difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.07,0:22:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Violet!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.97,0:23:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Subtitle translation by\NZensho Yamamoto
